# Testing Rules

## Commands

```bash
npm test           # Full suite (28 tests)
npm run test:watch # Watch mode
```

## Requirements for New Code

- New routes MUST have integration tests in `tests/`
- Test authorization denial paths, not just happy paths
- Use `request.agent(app)` for session-aware tests
- Mock Mapbox and Cloudinary — never call real APIs in CI

## Test Structure

```javascript
const request = require('supertest');
const app = require('../app');

describe('Feature', () => {
    test('description', async () => {
        const res = await request(app).get('/path');
        expect(res.statusCode).toBe(200);
    });
});
```

## Before Completing Any Task

Run `npm test` and confirm all tests pass.

Reference: `docs/testing/TESTING_AUDIT.md`, `docs/standards/TESTING_GUIDE.md`
